-- Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Petrobras Argentina and Tenaris
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-04-04T20:51:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-petrobras-argentina-and-tenaris.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  index fell 1.8 percent to 2,557.46.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  , Argentina’s largest lender by
market share, retreated 2.6 percent to 9.64 pesos in its fourth
day of losses. Local bank stocks fell in line with the slump in
global equities after the Federal Reserve said it may refrain
from more monetary stimulus, Carlos Aszpis, an equity strategist
at the brokerage Schweber & Cia. in Buenos Aires, said in a
phone interview.  Petrobras Argentina SA (PESA)   slumped 6.4 percent to
6.30 pesos, its biggest drop since March 6. The Argentine
province of Neuquen revoked an oil field concession from
 Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PBR) , which has a controlling stake in
Petrobras Argentina.  Tenaris SA (TEN)   slid 1.5 percent to 98.50 pesos. The
world’s largest producer of seamless steel tubes used in the oil
industry fell as crude declined.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
